Taylor Fry https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor_Fry 0 Taylor McQuiston Fry (born August 1, 1981) is a former American child actress. On film, Fry appeared in roles in Die Hard, North, and A Little Princess. On television, she has starring roles in Nightingales, Get a Life and Kirk. Fry graduated from Notre Dame High School in 1999, along with fellow actors Rami Malek and Rachel Bilson. She later attended and graduated from the University of California, Santa Barbara in 2003, where she became an avid Ultimate Frisbee player.
